Package: enum
Title: Enums in R
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Milan", "Malfait", , "m.malfait@ucl.ac.uk", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-9144-3701"))
Description: Provides a robust implementation of enumerations (enums) for R,
    enabling the creation of type-safe, validated sets of named constants.
    Enums help prevent errors by constraining variables to predefined values
    and offer better code readability and maintainability.
